Review: Mediocre burrito. SF is way better. Pineapple was interesting though! Decent serving size
Came with so many things and was super reasonably priced. Had cauliflower pita many dips the massoukeh! All super flavorful. the cheese borek was also AMAZING!
good vibes and really fun with view of the water!! crumble was also pretty good. pizza was good but not as good as the family owned pizza shop near by!

Hot take didn’t think it was that good. Got the eggplant, pita, halloumi, and cheese and falafel pizza. Falafel pizza was okay - cheese pizza was good, but nothing special. They didn’t give us pita or the dips everyone else was talking about. Halloumi was good but could’ve made the same from halloumi from Safeway. Overall underwhelmed based on all the 5s. Maybe would’ve been a 4 if I didn’t see the rest of the reviews hahaha
the food was really good here and was really large. Super filling and a great place for brunch in the area
didn’t really enjoy the appetizer or the pizza. the only good thing was the burger! but not worth the price premium. Good ambiance though
fried paneer taco!! it was really yummy and flavorful. had it as a drunchies and sober and both times were amazing
Spinach bialy and almond croissant!! Both were amazing!! LOVE THUS PLACE!
Long line, but moved quickly. Very filling and yummy!

the guac was so good! They make it tableside. The fajita burrito showed promise but I told them not to add random veggies but they added carrots and squash (blah) but the salsa was so good! May also be biased because Mexican food sucks in NJ
the bottomless was great with so many different flavors and they were super attentive. The food was just fine nothing special…
Kruthi took me here and forced me to try the rose ice cream, which I did, and it’s now my favorite ice cream of all times (maybe only second to cold stone cake batter)
A vegan healthy place! Nothing that was super great about it though…. Would only go back if friends wanted it or it was the only healthy option
@anika and @nikhil warned us that the one in sf had regressed in quality and that it potentially gave them food poisoning. Anoop found one in Menlo Park and it was amazing! Parents also loved it

came with kru kru @kruthi  

Fried risotto was so good (definitely on the smaller size though). Could’ve had three orders of this for dinner and been content.

Pineapple pizza was definitely good, but not the best best pizza ever. Crust was nice because it had parm cheese on top. Also got the blossom squash pasta, which was interesting and worked , but I like flour and water pasta more.

Not sure if I would crave the pizza like I do village square or Tony’s, but definitely a solid spot, but on the pricier end.

Long review because I felt like I have to justify the 4 after @ani glowing 5 star rec.

Also thank god we got the chili sauce on the side or I would’ve died.
fajitas burrito, guac, chips
SOOOO GOOD! Always a favorite!! They also have a cute outdoor seating area now, where we are. Split the baklava yogurt and it was great!
AWESOME GARLIC BREAD (and they give it to you for free). Everything else is mediocre at best

did takeout with kru and got dahi chaat, kachori chaat, kofta sizzler, paneer sizzler, and Manchurian sizzler. Wouldn’t get the Manchurian again. Paneer sizzler and kofta sizzler were good!! It traveled decently - when I microwaved for two minutes it was wayyyy better. I know the kachori chaat had promise but delivered terribly. Dahi chaat was whatever lol. Likely would be a 5 in person for the true sizzler experience

Good portion size… best pizza around Lawrence township but just decent in comparison to NYC. Their eggplant parm sandwich is fine. The bread is sort of stale and the parm is mostly just cheese. Best option around the boarding school though!

TERRIBLE BANH MI! NO COMPARISON TO MENDOS. Tofu was not flavorful. Bread wasn’t warm and there was no flavor to anything?? Literally ate the carrots and that’s it 

Also this was at smorgasburg so maybe it’s different in person! Also can’t find toastieland anywhere but anoop became a 5-year old and decided he wanted the rainbow grilled cheese. It was good, but nothing special.

Takeout was terrible wouldn’t go again tbh. Only
Go in person because I remember it being much better
Cool vibe but the food was just okay. I got the baked ziti veggie style and it was fine! Wouldn’t be mad if we had to go back because it was a cute place, but nothing to look forward to
Pretty dry croissant and didn’t really have any almond filling

Garlic bread was definitely very good! I got the pumpkin ravioli which was very good! But it was definitely really sweet…. The sauce was amazing and I soaked up every bit of it with my bread, but the ravioli got a little too sweet towards the end. Looking around the portion sizes were really big for all the other dishes!! I wish I would have gotten to split half and half with someone so then it would have been the perfect amount of ravioli. The lasagna looked AMAZING when it came out for another table!
Super healthy, filling, accessible, good before going out or for a chill meal.
best pizza is by far their potato or corn
Buttermilk bar and old fashioned. Honestly just fine lol. I don’t think I like donuts anymore 😀
Spinach salad, whipped feta, pita, falafel, and hummus! EVERYTHING WAS SO FLAVORFUL AND SO GOOD! Would definitely come back if in the area
Amazing goat cheese appetizer (and I don’t even like goat cheese). Fig pizza was the perfect crossover of village and lindustrie. Lovedddd the vodka pasta

Okay so I gave la fiesta a 5 but I think this is the real 5! I got a veggie guaggilo burrito and my dad got a veggie enchilada with mole and guagillo. I tried his mole and actually liked it - not sure if this one just didn’t have chocolate (??). The sauce was so unique and creamy and great! Didn’t love the chips that much probably bc I like flour tortilla chips more. Guac is made by me! We had to do order in Bc mom was struck by COVID.
paneer pinwheel is decent but nothing special. The appetizers are WAY better! I would go back and just do appetizers next time
The crepes were really really good! Nothing special about the mac and cheese! 2/3 blueberry pancakes were good but one was super burnt 😭
I swear I’m not inflating any of these. One of the best empanadas I’ve ever had. So flakey and perfect and the salsa was super flavorful

All were good items that were flavorful for fast food indian!! love the fusion concept. have also tried the pav bhaji which was good! would not get the bhel
puri again though — not super flavorful!
pumpkin eggplant enchilada… honestly one of the best enchiladas I’ve ever had.. also their wine was so good. Brussels sprouts were amazing
Their malai kofta is hands down the best (or second best) I’ve ever had!! Everything else is fine / typical Indian food.
2.5 nothing special for vegetarians. Not bad but would never willingly go
eggplant basil pie! i thought it was good and when air fried was much better. The pizza is definitely lighter on cheese, so may try the whit pizza next time. The crust was great!
Pasta comes with fried eggplant which was great and very flavorful. I got the personal size pizza and it was perfect to have with some pasta on the side. Thin crust and amazing!

Really good bagel place in NJ that may be better than Tompkins or really darn close! We had the avocado blast on an egg everything toast which was so big and awesome. Also tried the French toast bagel with crumb cake cream cheese. I loved the French toast bagel but wasn’t as excited about the cream cheese. It was good but nothing that was super amazing. Would 100% go back. Bagels were perfectly soft and chewy too.

THE EGGPLANT WAS SO GOOD!! The best eggplant I’ve ever had. The tie dye was so yummy too! The pizza is thin crust so did not feel gross after. The crust was burned but rest was great. I would skip on the white pizza next time but the 1/2 and 1/2 is a great way to try!

what a saga. We finally went and when I told my dad he said anoop and I may think it’s too spicy. We Called ahead and asked if they can make their stuff mild and they said yes but when we got there they said mostly everything was spicy. We ordered the pakora and we could barely eat it so we decided to leave. They were really nice about it and didn’t charge us but anoop left a nice tip! Really kind wait staff just wasn’t food we could’ve eaten 😢

lasagna tasting flight was amazing!! get the veggie one!! bruschetta was okay though - would skip. the focaccia crisps also looked really good. lost hearing because of the loud, annoying woman next to us…

I BEAT ANOOP
UNLIMITED PIZZA
SO GOOD
First meal back in sf! So good!
Murray the cop with garlic herb cream cheese! Perfected the savory breakfast bagel!!
Very good pancakes!! Would definitely come back to try some of their savory items.
Kru, anoop, and I came here during COVID era and it was really good! Drinks were cheap and strong and still tasted good. The nachos were really good too. Would coke again for drinks!!
Marionberry cheesecake. It was fine — wouldn’t go back for it. I think their honeycomb was really good the first time I went (pre taste) so will need to go back to retry!
food was fine not sure what the hype is about the place. Maybe need to come back for a full dinner. Drinks were interesting though
Don’t hate me but always a 5! First time trying dogpatch and by far the best souvla ever
super yummy and flavorful! One of the better pizzas I’ve had in sf. Comes second to Tony’s. The pizza here is better than the normal flour and water.

caveat! anoop was VERY thoughtful and picked these up for me before moving in, but thought the bagels were kinda hard and not soft and chewy like Tompkins. I do think the walnut cream cheese was good and the rainbow bagel was more promising. The everything bagel was not too great haha. We will have to go again because of all the 5 stars!
It was good! But definitely needed to split with someone or it would have been too sweet. Lots of variety!
Very creamy and very good! Usually split the large with two people and sometimes have leftovers. Doesn’t deliver well though so need to go in person
very good! they’re allowing for samples again!!

I wouldn’t get the fries again because it was nothing special. I came home and reheated in the oven and added salt and it was much better. The pita wrap was great with the halloumi. Will definitely be back for a healthy dinner!

Stopped by because we were hungry and got the chaat platter! It was pretty good. Corn one was too spicy. Bhel puri was good. @ani I feel like you would like the corn chaat because it was spicy haha. 

If I came back I would order the dahi chaat
Chilaquiles was so flavorful and filling and didn’t feel super heavy! The blonde was also really yummy and healthy tasting. Really hard to find a seat inside but great for pickup
sort of tomato soup like! nothing too great

Place: Lolita Cocina & Tequila Bar Fort Point
Review: IMMACULATE VIBES FOR A FRIDAY NIGHT! Make sure to make a reservation. All the food was really flavorful. We wanted to try a few other things but the waiter warned us it would be spicy so we stayed away. He made us a special veggie quesadilla though which was very accommodating. It is a bar that turns more and more into a club as the night goes on. I’m used to mediocre Mexican food, but this place did it right!
fine pizza. quickest thing open at 2am on 6th street. Would only go again if I needed it after drinking.
Had the carrot cake and tres leches! Carrot cake BLEW ME OUT OF THE WATER!! BEST DOUGHNUT EVER
Chole bhatura, random chaat, paneer roll

I originally wanted to go to wave street cafe but their wait was too long so we found this place. The egg was solid, pancakes were humongous and good, but kind of dry unless you got a piece with banana in it. I wouldn’t be mad to go back but wouldn’t seek it out

Pesto green machine classic. Nothing special about either of them. If I was tipsy I can see why it may taste good, but honestly wasn’t that great. I took a bite of the red and didn’t want anymore! The pesto was better, but still not that great!

IT WAS SO BAD! I WILL NEVER EVER GO AGAIN! I have never wanted to leave a place in the middle of a meal… we got the buffet and there were 5 veggie options and all of them were terrible. We heard some other people complaining about the food too… so sad that a favorite is now gone… I’m sure it’s still worth it in sf with bottomless…

The ambiance was super nice and service was quick and honestly they have happy hour until 8 everyday for 5 dollar pours. Idk why anoop and I still get “nice wine” when we can’t taste the difference and we also I  don’t love cheese plates so not sure why we got that either. Would definitely come again’ 

Tldr: if you have unrefined taste I’m sure you’ll love the place, If you’re picky with wine I have no idea! 

P.s. have to document my swollen eye
good vibes for bottomless in Berkeley and actually good food!
FORGOT PICTURES!

Falafel sandwich and pesto hummus. I don’t usually love falafel, but these ones were so good and flavorful! The pesto hummus was okay, wouldn’t get again. Healthy meal! Would recommend for a quick bite.
very good food! First time I went indoors. Really small indoor area so definitely need to make a reservation. Also tried the lychee drink which wasn’t too sweet and good!

Falafel sandwich. The falafels were really good but the sandwich itself was okay. Some of the sauces seemed to conflict with eachother. The fries were great and so was the garlic sauce. If I came again I would probably make my own sandwich with feta, olives, pickled vegetables, and garlic sauce. That would be a solid 4!

best malai kofta I’ve had on the east coast! We had the malai paneer too - that one was okay, but not tomato soup like at all! We also had the ragada pattie which was very flavorful. Best Indian food I’ve had here so far!

has the egg and cheese sandwich and the brown sugar ricotta toast this time!! had it in person and it was a game changer and bumped it to 5. The bagel came out steaming hot and the cheese was perfectly melted. The egg was actually much better hot!! Craving this place and we just left. @anoop has pictures
We went on a Saturday night and the ambiance was great. I got the Fresca drinks with mezcal and it was very good. Food was great!

dude the food in Austin is just amazing lol. Had the border salad (would have wished we asked for less dressing). Shared appetizers: fried okra, cauliflower, tofu, and Mac and cheese balls. Okra was good in theory but I thought it wasn’t amazing. Standouts were the tofu and salad. Would love to go back and great place to go bar hopping right after!

They only take cash! Sangria was great.
Wouldn’t get the bruschetta again — it was nothing special. The white pizza was good to split between two and very filling!
Calzone and pasta! Both were good and the ambiance outside was really nice! Not a place I would go out of my way to visit but always a solid option
Kachori chaat, malai kofta, naan. It was all fine. Nothing special. Not super flavorful either. Wouldn’t be mad if it was the only option, but wouldn’t go back

Same as the one on telegraph but so good! They have a really nice outdoor area too as long as no homeless people bother you. If you go around closing time they sometimes give you an extra half of a pizza!

ty @sid for being my partner in crime and convincing @ani to get the boom!! calzone was also so good! would skip on the cheese pizza next time. a solid 5 for the first two dishes mentioned. the two month wait was worth it!! 

“you mean we are getting pizza with just cheese???” - sid
got the everything bagel with cream cheese. Definitely not a Thompkins bagel but was soft and chewy!

Got the white square, garlic knots, and grandma. The garlic knots were not good (threw them away) BUT the white pizza was heavenly. Way better than rubirosas white pizza. The grandma was good but the white pizza was definitely the highlight.

All the food was really good and they let you pick between garlic or regular naan!! Yay! Lots of
options (especially for veggie)

Came here with anoop to celebrate!! 

Had the four cheese pasta which was good, but wouldn’t crave it. The mac and cheese balls were awesome! The drinks were huge and got me drunk! The view of the city is beautiful. 

We had a Uber incident which meant I never got a cheesecake, but anoop did…. on the day we were supposed to celebrate ME…. Classic…
Adding pictures this time
French cream bread is my favorite thing ever!! No other baked good will really compare. The bread is incredibly soft and the custard is VERY GOOD! Savory breads are also great!

really soft and good in person (especially with ice cream)! Always get three to go and always so
good once warmed up!
didn’t really think any of the food was super flavorful. the ambiance is great though
both were fine but the vibes were really good!

place was cute and the menu was diverse and interesting. Loved the concept of a sweet potato tartine but it wasn’t as flavorful. Flour and tatte usually go head to head but I think flour was much better! Still great food. The coffee cake was a 10/10
White spinach pizza and caprese. Both were just fine… honestly the caprese was on the verge of a 2… the white pizza was a 3.. I think the rating is only good because people go drunk????

wonderful food and ambiance! The wait staff is also really nice! They made me a sweet cocktail off the menu and let me try it a couple times before I loved it. The eggplant was yummy (but doesn’t come with pasta). Really flavorful and not spicy at all! the arancini was okay. The bread and butter was some of the best I’ve had!
fries weren’t good but the Mac and cheese was very flavorful and filling!! No special ambiance or anything though.
Really good place for brunch. It’s near the park so you can go there afterwards. Overall quick service and tasty.

super strong 4! Did family style with Anjali Christian and anoop. They were nice enough to go veggie and everything was really good. Just don’t think I would crave it like I do the one flour and water pasta dish.
the bagels are really good!!! not as much cream cheese selections but super soft bagels

WHAT IS AUSTIN??? I was hoping this would be a 4 for diversity BUT ANOTHER 5!! Burrito was SO GOOD! Beans were actually flavorful and vegetarian and the secret bummer sauce was so unique and brought the entire burrito together!!! Anjali got the hot sauce and said it was good, but didn’t try because spice tolerance lol.
One of the best ice cream I’ve ever had. Gooey cake
Not spicy at all and very good for “Indian fast food”. Definitely one of my favorite places!
SWEET POTATO FALAFEL WAS AMAZING! Would not get the fried eggplant again. I think only the sweet potato falafel may be good here

The vibes were great! Each group got their own fire pit overlooking the golf course. We got the balloon bread, pizza, and strawberry balsamic dessert. All it was really good and vibes were great. Wouldn’t crave it so it’s not a 5.
This was bad! No flavor at all. Threw most of it away. Would not go again
Forgot the pictures! Whoops!
Could’ve been a 5… think it just needed more cream cheese haha

We got the veg Manchuria, paneer tikka, malai kofta, ghee toast, masala dosa, and mango lassi. Everything was amazing and had a unique flavor. One of the top Indian places I’ve had. Definitely top 3! It’s sort of quiet inside, but they have nonstop delivery so you know it’s well loved!
the glaze was good but the donut was sort of just fine. Also don’t think I’m a fan of normal donuts (prefer old fashioned which are denser)
Butter cake ice cream with funfetti or snickerdoodle cookie!! Cookie melts in your mouth and ice cream is perfect!
Vegan sushi sounds weird, but after I had it I was sold. Amazing food but slightly expensive.
Such a great experience. Got too full. Will need to go texas annually to visit!
Needed late night ice cream and they were the only ones open. I had butter pecan and cake batter and both just tasted like vanilla… it was good vanilla ice cream but not what I was expecting..

Was about to not taste this place on @anoop and my pizza tasting tour, but thank god I did! Got the burrata eggplant and drizzled honey sauce over it! It was so so so good!! Thank you @ani for the rec!!
Such a great vibe inside and really nice wait staff. The burgers are pretty big and really filling. One of the better veggie burgers I’ve had in a while
best samosa I’ve ever had haha! pad Thai in person was great but didn’t travel well
Very yummy and interesting use of pineapple! 100% would go again and again. Cute vibe and also great for big parties!

I think now that I’ve had more New York food this is definitely a 4, but a really strong 4! The pitchers were SUPER big and cheap and honestly I really liked my vodka pasta and anoops ravioli. I wouldn’t get the eggplant again!
SO GOOD! Would definitely get strawberry cream cheese again. Honestly nothing seems bad at this place…
Maple walnut ice cream is amazing! It’s been a while but I would definitely go back and try others!
Veggie sandwich and salad with Greek goddess dressing. Massive portion sizes - especially with their honey wheat bread!! The tofu is divine. Love this place.

Appetizers were so amazing… literally dreaming about the focaccia and arancini. The long pasta was just okay, but the saffron pasta was solid (but lindens ravioli was better). Also felt a tad rushed at the place, but overall glad we went, but would t go again!
Murray the cop and French toast with walnut raisin!  Murray the cop is my new favorite savory!!
Probably a hot take, but got the wet burrito with Oaxaca cheese. It was sooo good! But I know others don’t like it as much 🥹
Coffee cake was good, but the sweet potato sandwich wasn’t as good as the melt I got last time. Would definitely stick to the seasonal veggie melts!
Very good and always wonderful when I eat it right outside the ferry building!! One of my go to places for a Saturday Sunday snack!!
Cool bar, really good music! Lots of dancing too
Best pasta I’ve had in SF. Pretty pricey given small portions, but well worth it. Pizza isn’t as good as the pasta.
white pizza and margarita. Got a slice of both and split with @anoop . Both were very very good. Definitely on the heavier side
Great place for drinks in sf! Beautiful view and good food and drinks. Definitely on the pricier side though.
Got the ricotta pancakes and wanted to cry it was so bad. Anoop and I were en route to souvla when he begged me to change my mind. Restaurant choosing privileges should’ve been revoked…

The broccoli melt was FANTASTIC!! Great portion size and was very flavorful. The panini was served hot! The sticky bun was amazing as well! Get it warmed up!! Definitely will be back as much as possible. Very busy cafe so expect to wait around for a table or go to Harvard campus to eat
Drinks were really good but the food was just fine for being vegetarian. Maybe I didn’t order the right things?

one of the better Indian places I’ve had at Berkeley! Cheap and flavorful if you get the malai kofta or saag paneer. Mango lassi is also great! Don’t think the paneer tikka is good - tastes slightly like tomato soup?

I loved the French toast bagel (again!!). Savory cream cheese was great but wouldn’t get it with avocado again. It was too overpowering and hard to taste the rest of the bagel 😢 BUT still a favorite go to spot.
malai kofta was sort of tomato soup like! would not go back again
Banana pudding! It was good, but I wouldn’t crave it. Definitely should go once
Went in person and the garlic naan was SO fluffy and soft!! The malai kofta was amazing too!! Wouldn’t get the malai marke paneer again though! Go to Indian spot now!

Dahi puri, kale pakora, malai kofta, paneer. The Dahi puri was good and the malai kofta was great and not spicy. The kale pakora was fine - looked prettier than it was. Didn’t love the paneer. Ambiance was great and the people gave us an extra chicken biryani because they made an extra. Also the wine pours were great. But anoop didn’t like it and is convinced he can’t eat Indian food anymore 😢

Sicilian pizza and pesto pomodoro pizza. It was so good, fresh, and light. The pesto pomodora was the clear winner (I chose it, of course). The Sicilian was far from bad — was really good too — but was unanimously agreed to be second by the family (another data point for why anoop can’t choose anything). We also got the gnocchi appetizer which was very unique and good! The mushroom flavor came through!! Overall great place and great outdoor seating.
Malai kofta and paneer tikka masala. This one is closer to lville and we did takeout. It delivered well and was really yummy. The inside was not nearly as nice as the Somerville option.
Bottomless drinks and food! The pita was so soft and the other stuff was amazing.
some veggie pasta and appetizers. The food wasn’t that great for veg people but the ambiance was great! Open kitchen that I was amazed by
Good bagels. Loved the olive pimento cream cheese. Thompkins is still better, but maybe if we got the hash brown it would’ve solidified the 5.
cake batter doughnado! Was fine - wouldn’t go again!

Have had both of these burritos! They are AMAZING, very filling, and come with a side of rice and beans. This is hands down the best Mexican I’ve had because of how flavorful it is! The puya is their second spiciest but i was still able to handle it (has a little bit of a kick).
enchiladas were fine but the nachos and burritos were way better. Their salsa bar is also awesome!! So many different options. Love it!
solid egg sandwich! Wouldn’t crave though
Best chaat place I’ve ever had. The owners know my dad and always ask if my spice tolerance has gone up lol but they make everything extra sweet for me!! Favorite is bhel puri and kachori chaat
Malai kofta is the best I’ve had in sf! Have to get it mild though because I’m a wimp.

I had the BYO salad: spinach, whipped feta, tzatiki, falafel, pickled onions, olives, red cabbage, lentil, and garlic sauce with a side of pita chips. It was all super yummy and flavorful and clean!! i haven’t liked falafels for a while but this one was really good!! Pita chips were amazing!

breakfast sandwich and DKA! I wouldn’t get the DKA again but the croissant sandwich was the best I’ve had! Very flakey on the outside and soft on the inside!! I loved the olive oil and herbs on top. I just would always prefer a bagel over this so giving it a 4 because Thompkins was a 5.
Just got chips and queso but best queso I’ve had so far
Such a soft chewy waffle. Got the frozen pre pack and had some at home and it was so good.
I’ve had their pumpkin flavors and butter pecan. Both are very very good!! And huge portions! Definitely on the heavier side though!

standout was the Parker rolls and ravioli. Wouldn’t get the pomodoro again but it was definitely fresh and light. 

If I went back I’d want to try some other apps and the pizza. 

Service was phenomenal!! And they gave anoop free bday cookies YAY!
ROTI AND DIPPING SAUCE IS MY FAVORITE! My parents and I will all get our own and share a main dish. The pad Thai is good but nothing special.

we went to the cafe on the first floor and got the mushroom, olive, and margerita pizza. So good and the crust was really fluffy. The grocery store was insane. The pesto sauce is one of the best I’ve had. Also had so many pasta shapes!! So fun!
It’s like they knew we were coming!! Potato and corn pizza. Beautiful on all accounts.
massive crumb cake was fine but fun to get with friends haha and super cheap. BEST donut holes and old fashioned donut ever
cake batter yogurt (fat free too!) very tasty and light!!

excellent place in philly!! the highlight was the kale salad and sweet potato. Also honestly the mushroom toast was fantastic so I can’t even pick. So flavorful and the waiter took such good care of us. Loved every minute of this dinner!
the drinks were fine but nothing special. There weren’t many vegggie options, but I split the flautas and guac with friends. It was just fine!! Nice ambiance though
So so so good!! And the ricotta on top is the best addition. It’s seasonal though so would only go when it’s on the menu
malai kofta was good but the paneer tikka tasted a little like tomato soup. one of the better malai kodtas in the city
SO GOOD SO BIG!! the best!
BOTH WERE SO GOOD AND SO FILLING!! Dined indoors and was a super cute place. Wasn’t able to finish the entire thing but it warmed up well for leftovers
the veggie empanada was terrible - we threw it away. The guava and cheese was much better but the outer texture wasn’t fluffy and soft like the one I had in Austin!
Got the fries. Crispy and solid @anoop thought it was spicy but he would think ice cream is spicy at this point
Cannoli was fine. Not that special. Mikes was way better!
the chaat was really good (needed to specify mild spice). The rose lassi is very sweet. The malai kofta and paneer masala were fine! Would come back for the street food not the main Indian food

pretzel bread, whipped feta, kung pau cauliflower, and Thai noodle salad! Everything was SOOOO GOOD! stand outs were the pretzel bread and kung pau cauliflower. Even the salad was super yummy and the peanuts added a nice crunch and was very flavorful and light. The tofu wasn’t breaded but very crispy. Love this place but definitely expensive - not sure if I would go for dinner on my own money, but would def go for drinks and apps

great place that was fairly crowded for lunch on Saturday! No reservations though. Wait staff was really attentive. The pasta was really flavorful and all the plates are super cheap. Pitcher was super strong. Entire family couldn’t finish it!

Had the breakfast quesadilla and shared French toast sticks! Quesadilla was really filling and good - avocado was kind of random though. French toasts stocks were also good but would’ve been to heavy with just that!! Good vibes probably good for bottomless!

egg sandwich and artichoke boreka. both were really yummy!! the Jerusalem bagel itself was so chewy and soft — the cheese they used was interesting. They made their eggs fluffy which I don’t love as much as normal which is the only reason it’s not a 5 because I wouldn’t crave it as much.

The boreka was so soft and flaky and also good!! 

The Jerusalem bagel in picture is only 1/2 of it. 

Also way better than mala project 😊
Ugh best red sauce pizza I’ve add!! Better than John’s!
Really good for going out with friends or out on a date. Great drinks that are reasonably priced. Very good pizza, probably best I’ve had in SF.
caveat I don’t like t chocolate so couldn’t have their famous flavor. Got a butter pecan and it was fine - didn’t see the hype
Best Indian I’ve had in SF, medium priced and great value. Wouldn’t go there for ambiance though, but great for takeout.

I actually went to the one in Austin but it’s not showing up… probably because it just opened! But such a cool concept. It’s unlimited pizza and servers walk around within 15 types of pizzas and give you a small slice and you can even request more. The staff was super nice and even made some special veggie ones when they learned I was vegetarian. Standouts we’re the corn, mushroom vodka, guava dessert pizza, and dulce de leche dessert pizza.

solid but wouldn’t crave or seek out. Got the eggplant panini and thought it would come with bread not burger bread. May have ordered something different if I knew. It was sort of small portions too. Underwhelmed but they let us stay for 4 hours so good spot for what we needed

wow… contrary to my original opinion i think sweetgreen is better than mixt!! got a create your own: spinach, red onions, cabbage, crispy rice, broccoli, avo, sweet potato, tofu, mushroom, and ginger dressing.

everything was really good!! wouldn’t get avocado next time but the rest of it was fabulous and flavorful… cannot believe I have been converted!!
nothing special about the food but good vibes for bottomless
SO GOOD and the best place to eat during the workday. Easy to pick up!!! No indoor dining.
honestly may even be better than the tacos in Austin. Got the mushroom tacos and sweet potato burrito. Both were fabulous. Ty @gita for the rec!!
Yummy pizza after drinking!
okay food but I was vegetarian at a steakhouse lol
CYO stir fry! I got a coconut curry noodle with veggies tofu and egg. Quick fast casual!
BOTH are so so good! It’s more of a grocery store take out type deal. Always have to ask for mild though!
ALWAYS HIT THE SPOT
This is one of the few pizza places where I don’t feel like shit after. I wont go there in person unless they open indoor seating.

The rumali roti is so lovely!! So big and light. Have never had anything like it before! The veg kofta is so good and doesn’t make me feel gross after even though it’s probably all cream. The rest of the food is always really flavorful. Their paneer wrap is more indo Chinese but comes with the rumali roti so can’t complain!
Some days it’s really good, but other days it’s overloaded with salt. Mango salsa is really good. Ambiance and drinks are great.
Have some of the best salsas I’ve had!  Only good cheese enchilada I’ve had in the city which actually has a lot of flavor to it! Always crowded on Friday and Saturday nights
Margherita pizza! It was fine, nothing great, but wouldn’t be mad if I had to go
Such a good meal, especially when looking for a healthy option on a weeknight!!
I got the grilled cheese and tomato soup and it was such a classic done well!! Came with @anoop  when we went to Carmel ages ago
Really good ice cream, mid tier prices. I like sampling the flavors because they are so interesting. You won’t get them anywhere else.
Really long line so plan ahead! The DKA bad croissant were so good! Grilled cheese was one of the best I’ve had. Cute outdoor seating.
LOVE ALL OF THESE!! I have literally zero restraint when I walk into this store. You can’t go wrong with whatever you pick!
Way too sweet and the cupcakes were mostly frosting. I got the cream filled and strawberry shortcake. Both were mediocre. Wouldn’t go again!

oh my GOD! After everyone was raving about farmhouse I thought I just didn’t like Thai food but this place proved me wrong. We went with shaans parents and got three appetizers and a main entree. The paratha was soft and flaky, peanut sauce was very flavorful, and the Tom kha soup was so hearty. But the corn fritters stole the show. The perfect amount of sweet and savory. The green curry entree was good! I typically don’t like curry but I liked this one. We were full on appetizers so decided against pad Thai which is my normal so would love to come back and try it. Will be dreaming about the corn fritters until I come back….
Great deal 4-8 is buy one get one free so we had 4 drinks for 30 dollars! Good vibe and good music. Kitchen was closed so they let us get outside food
did a goldbelly order here and got the following: salted caramel, rose, ghee and roti, mango, and confetti. The confetti wasn’t great but the rest were yummy. The standout was the gulab jamun cake!
Solid Indian pizza. Wouldn’t go on a date there though because ambiance isn’t great. Better for takeout.
AMAZING PIZZA! Got the white pizza and the grandma. Both were squares. The pizza itself was light and fluffy. Ricotta and cheese was sooo flavorful! Will definitely be back!
Artichoke dip was great!!! Surprisingly cheese pizza was the best thing haha. Good vibes too!
had to leave the restaurant because I got too drunk… but the food I had after I recovered was too spicy and not really that great. Wouldn’t go again!
Really good for grab and go food
The extra orange sauce is really yummy and not too spicy! The burrito was okay but the quesadilla was great! Would definitely go back for the quesadilla

Hottest of hot takes!!! The scallion pancakes were honestly just okay and didn’t taste like much. The veg dumplings were just bad. The fried noodles were good but nothing super special. Unfortunately, need to give this a 3 BUT two positives: Village square pizza saved the day AND anoop lost restaurant picking privileges forever :)
too much cheese on this pizza that it became overwhelming. Maybe would be better if I just had the normal margerita pizza
LOOK AT THAT CROSS SECTION!! Croissant literally melts in your mouth and the almond filling is divine. Best almond croissant thus far
all the cookies are so soft and dense!! ice cream is pretty good too! should probably not eat an entire one but always can’t resist LOL
Blondie, snickerdoodle, and apple crisp. Apple crisp was bad but the blondie was phenomenal!! Snickerdoodle warmed up was even better!!

Vodka pasta and cheesy bread. The cheesy bread was amazing but the vodka pasta wasn’t that great. We did do a catering order so maybe going there would be better…. I would go again and dine in and see if it’s any better.
The burrito is better than la Vik’s but still not the best burrito. I’ve heard it’s really good with chicken. The quesadilla is pretty small. The sauce is also on the spicier side but my mom loves it
